Steps for PetaLinux project

petalinux-create --type project --template zynqMP --name RECONOS

petalinux-config --get-hw-description <PATH-TO-XSA Directory>
//XSA exported from tf-reconos build.hw (2020.1 toolchain)
adjust DTG->Machine name to zcu102 board

adjust petalinux-config by hand (following previous design)
    enable kernel autoconfig, uboot autoconfig
    manual kernel boot args: "earlycon clk_ignore_unused root=/dev/nfs nfsroot=192.168.2.41:/home/fepaje/WD/reconos64/nfs,tcp,nfsvers=3 ip=dhcp rw"
    enable fpga-manager
    (?)leave uboot config target on default (other, xilinx_zynqmp_virt_defconfig), previous project was different (zcu102 target)
    image packing: switch to NFS with corresponding path/ip, disable tftpboot copy

//create kernel module
petalinux-create -t modules --name reconosmod64 --enable

copy in driver source code
adjust makefile (copy from previous)
adjust recipe file .bb (copy from previous)

//configure device-tree

    ??? not needed ???
    auto devictree inferred from hw platform is put into pl.dtbo overlay (support for overlays not enabled by default)
    -> modify system-user.dtsi (copy from previous)
        -> "amba" instead of "amba_pl@0" !! change of naming convention!!

//configure kernel
petalinux-config -c kernel
    leave default for now

//configure rootfs
petalinux-config -c rootfs
    leave default (module was already enabled)

//build
petalinux-build

    or only for module: petalinux-build -c reconosmod64

//package
use shellscript for petalinux-package command

//deploy
copy to SD: BOOT.BIN, boot.scr, image.ub
copy to NFS, then "chmod 777 -R *" to avoid permission errors


//clean (before checkin)
petalinux-build -f -x mrproper

    or only for module: petalinux-build -c reconosmod64 -x clean